00:26:36,820 --> 00:26:38,720
 And I'm screaming and screaming.

540
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:43,700
 And I'm so loud that all the other seminary students

541
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,620
 drop their books, come out of their dormitories,

542
00:26:46,620 --> 00:26:48,820
 into the field going, what's going on?

543
00:26:48,820 --> 00:26:50,660
 I lost Tyson.

544
00:26:50,660 --> 00:26:52,640
 And then everyone's looking for Tyson.

545
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,940
 We're at the soccer field, the football field,

546
00:26:54,940 --> 00:26:57,420
 the playground, inside the slides, in the tunnels,

547
00:26:57,420 --> 00:27:00,420
 in the forest, everywhere, in the crosswalk,

548
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:02,940
 everywhere, no sign of him.

549
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:05,140
 I am starting to panic.

550
00:27:05,140 --> 00:27:08,060
 The worst like comes to mind.

551
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:09,620
 Oh my goodness, he was abducted.

552
00:27:09,620 --> 00:27:11,300
 I don't know by what, a coyote?

553
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:12,260
 I'm not sure.

554
00:27:12,260 --> 00:27:16,540
 But in my head, it was like worst possible thing.

555
00:27:16,540 --> 00:27:20,380
 I go around the apartment building and I see him there.

556
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:23,060
 He's just sitting on the step waiting for me.

557
00:27:23,060 --> 00:27:25,340
 I run to him and I grab him

558
00:27:25,340 --> 00:27:28,180
 and I'm rejoicing inside to tears.

559
00:27:28,180 --> 00:27:31,060
 I pick him up and I just run around everywhere.

560
00:27:31,060 --> 00:27:32,660
 I found him, I found him, I found him.

561
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:35,780
 And everyone is celebrating with me.

562
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:40,880
 So if you ask me, was I glad and happy

563
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:43,620
 that Ethan didn't wander off?

564
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:45,220
 Of course.

565
00:27:45,220 --> 00:27:48,460
 But was I happier that I found Tyson?

566
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:50,740
 Most definitely, right?

567
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:52,580
 So even though I've never heard a sheep,

568
00:27:52,580 --> 00:27:55,820
 a tended sheep or even one touch them,

569
00:27:55,820 --> 00:28:00,420
 this story I get, I can relate to it.

570
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:01,780
 I identify.

571
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:06,020
 Because you see, the parable of the lost sheep,

572
00:28:06,020 --> 00:28:08,460
 as told in Luke, did not do that to me.

573
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:09,740
 I didn't think of that.

574
00:28:09,740 --> 00:28:12,260
 Because there was not that whole section

575
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:15,220
 about Jesus talking about how important children are.

576
00:28:15,220 --> 00:28:16,100
 Right?

577
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:17,920
 It didn't hit me in the same way.

578
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:20,120
 So if we look at this,

579
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:22,920
 the components within the components of Mark,

580
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:27,920
 you'll see that he actually uses a different voice

581
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:30,560
 because his disciples are basically bickering.

582
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:31,640
 Who's better?

583
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,680
 And I experience that all the time with my children.

584
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:34,520
 Who's better?

585
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:35,340
 I'm better, I'm better.

586
00:28:35,340 --> 00:28:36,180
 No, I'm better.

587
00:28:36,180 --> 00:28:37,000
 No, you're not.

588
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:37,840
 Yes, I am.

589
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:41,160
 The point is, there's a bigger plot.

590
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:44,580
 He's settling the rivalry between them with this parable.

591
00:28:44,580 --> 00:28:48,500
 And he's saying, all you need to do is be like children.

592
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:52,060
 But I wanna also highlight,

593
00:28:52,060 --> 00:28:55,260
 he's pretty casual when he tells the parable,

594
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:57,380
 but he's pretty disciplinary

595
00:28:57,380 --> 00:28:59,520
 when he tells them about children.

596
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:01,700
 And here's like the tone,

597
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:04,860
 unless you change, you're not gonna get this.

598
00:29:04,860 --> 00:29:07,360
 And it's about my father and your father.

599
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:11,260
 In Luke, Jesus didn't do that.

600
00:29:11,260 --> 00:29:12,100
 Right?

601
00:29:12,100 --> 00:29:14,140
 He didn't say your father, my father.

602
00:29:14,140 --> 00:29:15,360
 He used heavens.

603
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,460
 There was no personal relationship there.

604
00:29:18,340 --> 00:29:21,140
 And also in Luke, he says,

605
00:29:21,140 --> 00:29:24,300
 suppose one of you owned a hundred sheep.

606
00:29:24,300 --> 00:29:27,220
 In this one, he said, suppose a man.

607
00:29:27,220 --> 00:29:28,200
 Well, why?

608
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:30,460
 Why are there these differences?

609
00:29:30,460 --> 00:29:32,500
 Because it's a different audience.

610
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:35,260
 The disciples are not wealthy people.

611
00:29:35,260 --> 00:29:37,940
 They would never own a hundred sheep, right?

612
00:29:37,940 --> 00:29:39,420
 But why does that matter?

613
00:29:39,420 --> 00:29:42,860
 It matters a lot because within that context,

614
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:46,660
 it tells a storyteller how to modify the story

615
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:49,920
 to make it impactful for whoever's listening.

616
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,760
 Right?

617
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:55,620
 And then later he was also saying,

618
00:29:55,620 --> 00:29:59,420
 you just have to be, you just have to be like children.

619
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:02,320
 So in that context,

620
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:07,320
 I don't think that Jesus is particularly condemning,

621
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:12,400
 but really teaching.

622
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:16,740
 So if we take a look at those two zoomed out storylines,

623
00:30:16,740 --> 00:30:19,680
 side by side, let's compare them.

624
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:23,360
 And I wanna focus a lot on the audience.

625
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:26,360
 So we've talked about a bunch of these already before,

626
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:29,200
 but I wanna focus on the audience.

627
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:33,160
 In Luke, there's these Pharisees

628
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:35,880
 and these religious leaders, right?

629
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:39,520
 And as much as he's being clever and witty,

630
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,540
 kind of tongue in cheek,

631
00:30:41,540 --> 00:30:43,520
 he's basically trying to show them

632
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:44,920
 that the gates of heaven are welcome

633
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:47,240
 to people they don't expect.

634
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:49,920
 And the leaders wanna gatekeep it,

635
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:53,280
 but Jesus is saying, no, as long as there's repentance,

636
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,080
 there's acceptance.

637
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:57,240
 And for some of us here,

638
00:30:57,240 --> 00:31:00,840
 maybe we're grumbling about someone or something.

639
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:03,840
 I know I sure am a lot of times

640
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:08,160
 when I think those people can't have access

641
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,560
 to the kingdom of heaven.

642
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:12,580
 Those people, the conniving people,

643
00:31:12,580 --> 00:31:15,980
 the self-righteous people, the rude people,

644
00:31:15,980 --> 00:31:20,460
 the exclusive people.

645
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:22,620
 And then I'm thinking, oh, wait a minute.

646
00:31:22,620 --> 00:31:25,260
 Am I being exclusive here?

647
00:31:25,260 --> 00:31:26,820
 So there's a compelling moment

648
00:31:26,820 --> 00:31:28,380
 and you're convicted, right?

649
00:31:28,380 --> 00:31:33,220
 Now in Mark, even though Jesus is directly talking

650
00:31:33,220 --> 00:31:38,220
 to the disciples and teaching them, disciplining them,

651
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:42,360
 he told them to be like children,

652
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:45,880
 even though they were acting like kids, ironically.

653
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:48,680
 But I don't think he was condemning his disciples either,

654
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:50,640
 but really helping them to solve their problem

655
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:51,480
 and their debate.

656
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,640
 And it's subtle, but actually not so subtle.

657
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:56,180
 If they're just like children,

658
00:31:56,180 --> 00:31:58,320
 their father's not gonna let any of them perish.

659
00:31:58,320 --> 00:31:59,820
 They're just chill out.

